**Land of Ṭá** – Ṭihrán (Tehran). Identified as the "Mother of the World" and the "Dayspring of Light," this city is the birthplace of the Manifestation of God’s glory.

**Land of Bahá** – Ṭihrán (Tehran). This designation arises from the numerical equivalence between the letters of "Bahá" and "Ṭ" (the first letter of Ṭihrán) in the generative geometry of the Revelation.

**Land of Yá** – Yazd. Bahá’u’lláh addresses the people of this land, stating that "heedlessness hath seized all the inhabitants of earth save whom God... hath willed."

**Land of Zá** – Zanján. This region is described as being "leavened with pure blood," where thousands sacrificed their lives to "exalt the mighty, most great Cause."

**Land of Khá** – Khurásán. Bahá’u’lláh proclaims: "We hear from thee the voice of heroes, raised in glorification of thy Lord."

**Land of Ṣád** – Iṣfahán. This land is celebrated as the "repository of His names and attributes, next to the sacred and specially designated lands."

**Land of Mím** – Mázandarán. This is the ancestral homeland of Bahá’u’lláh, specifically the district of Núr, where the "Sun of Truth... ancient native soil" is found.

**Land of Qáf** – The Caucasus region. It is traditionally identified as the "nest of the Símurgh and dwelling of the Phoenix of the East."

**Isle of Qáf** – Cyprus. Designated in some contexts as "Satan’s Isle," where the "Evil Whisperer" was relegated.

**Land of Qáf and Váv** – Qúchán.

**Land of Káf and Rá** – Karbilá. This "land of Káf and Rá" is a station which the ‘ulamás of the past "failed during all this time to comprehend."

**Zawrá** – Baghdád. Designating the "Abode of Peace," it is the site of the "Most Great House of God" and the "City of God."

**Land of Mystery (Arḍ-i-Sirr)** – Adrianople (Edirne). Bahá’u’lláh prophesied that this land would "pass out of the hands of the king" and its "course of things shall be altered."

**Point between the Two Seas** – Constantinople (Istanbul). This refers to the city situated between the Mediterranean and the Black Sea, where "the throne of tyranny" was once established.

**Land of Há and Mím** – Hamadán.

**Land of Fá** – Fárs (Shíráz). In the Revelation of the Bayán, this land became the "dayspring of the lands," just as Mecca had been in the Revelation of the Furqán.

**Land of Shín** – Shíráz. As the birthplace of the Primal Point, its "nightingale’s song reached the seven climes" and its air is "joyous and exhilarating."

**White Spot / Holy Valley** – ‘Akká. Often termed the "Most Great Prison," this spot is also identified as the "Banquet-Hall of God" where the "Lord of Lords" arrived in truth.

**Land of Bá** – Possibly where Bahá’u’lláh was after the Kitáb-i-Aqdas. ‘Akká was part of the Syrian Vilayet until 1888, then became part of the new Beirut Vilayet. ‘Abbás Effendi said the Land of Bá is Beirut, the city, to support a claim of being a prophesied leader of God.

**Land of Alif** – Ádhirbáyján. Bahá’u’lláh addressed the "heroes" of this land, affirming that its mountain "also has its portion" of the Divine Revelation.

**Fárán** – A region specifically named by the "Blessed Tongue" of Bahá’u’lláh. It is described as a clime where the "fire of divine love must surge so intensely that it brings warmth to all neighboring regions."

**Land of Alif and Rá** – Rasht and its surrounding territories.
